During a press gaggle aboard Air Force One en route to Johannesburg, South Africa, Press Secretary Jay Carney and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Ben Rhodes provided updates on the President's recent calls to lawmakers regarding immigration reform. They also discussed the strategy for garnering support in the House and highlighted the economic benefits of passing the immigration reform bill. Additionally, they mentioned the President's state dinner in Senegal and his upcoming town hall with young African leaders in Soweto. They also addressed questions about Sasha's absence from events, the President's encounter with a long-lost friend from Spain, and the inclusion of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs) in the administration's exchange program. Finally, Rhodes discussed the historical significance of the University of Capetown and addressed concerns about the absence of a delegation of black leaders on the trip.